titleStmt.title: The case of divers persons entitled to the benefit of articles, proclamations, and declarations, &c. in Ireland; in relation to a bill for vacating all grants of estates and other interests forfeited in Ireland, since the thirteenth day of February, one thousand six hundred and eighty eight: and for appropriating the same to the use of the publick, now lying before the honourable the House of Commons; humbly offer'd to the consideration of the said House.
